cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the use of social tags for resource classification, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also analyzes the effect of settings on tag distributions in folksonomies, which relates to social networks (cs.SI) and social data (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses user behavior (cs.HC) and the structure of folksonomies (cs.CY).
